original_reasoning:
Okay, let me see. I need to complete the Java code for the CaffeineDemo class. The task is to fill in the missing line where the comment says to manually clean up the cache. The comment mentions removing entries that are expired or evicted.

So, looking at the Caffeine Cache documentation, I remember that the Cache interface has a method called cleanUp(). This method is used to perform any pending maintenance operations, like evicting entries that have expired or are over the size limit. Since the user has already set up the cache with a maximum size and expiration, calling cleanUp() would trigger the cleanup process.

The existing code does everything else: putting values, getting, invalidating, etc. The last step before the TODO is invalidateAll(), which clears everything. But the comment says to manually clean up, so even after invalidateAll, maybe there are some pending operations. The cleanUp() method is usually called automatically by the cache, but if you want to trigger it manually, you do it here.

So the missing line should be cache.cleanUp();
